2012-12-24|2012-12-30.description: Lex goes on the offensive to find out more about his forgotten past. Meanwhile, in Paris, Superman and Impulse fight an unlikely group of art thieves. But when Impulse's powers are pushed to the max, he must face his biggest fear.

2012-01-30|2012-02-05.description:
The Invisible Woman clashes with the Sub-Mariner as war breaks out beneath the ocean! The armies of the Negative Zone attack! Mr Fantastic matches wits with Galactus!

Also: classic 1960s action! The Thing becomes Ben Grimm again – just as the Wizard strikes!

Includes material reprinted from Fantastic Four #585-586 and Fantastic Four #78.

2012-02-13|2012-02-19.description: When you move to strike Empress Sonja you had better not miss, because you only get one shot. Then it is her turn. Meanwhile Xander and Melea penetrate Koliostri's growing cult, and learn its secrets.

2012-02-20|2012-02-26.description: BRAND NEW ARC! GREAT FOR NEW READERS! Max Damage has seemingly driven Plutonian from Coalville, finally cementing him as a hero among the struggling desperate populace. But at what cost? And when the deal he made with Plutonian comes due, can Max be the hero that Coalville needs once again? Don’t miss the beginning of a new era in this companion to Mark Waid’s Eisner-nominated superhero series, IRREDEEMABLE!

Kyoko’s having trouble getting into the role of Cain’s sister. But is it because she can’t relate to a spoiled punk princess, or because she can’t let go of the fact that Ren is playing Cain? And Ren faces his own challenge with the situation. Can he stand to have the woman he loves treat him like a brother?

Concluding Open Contract, The Story Of The Forgiven.

The Marvel U’s Deadliest Assassins Have Been Sent After The Forgiven…And Are Trying To Kill Jubilee!

Guest-Starring Lady Bullseye, The Assassin’s Guild, And Lord Deathstrike
Deadshot pleads his case to Penguin as to why he should be the next member of his team. Can Deadshot's dramatic tale of a horrific childhood buy his way on to Penguin's team...and into his armory?
2012-04-16|2012-04-22.name: Operation: Kill Joker (Part Two)

2012-04-23|2012-04-29.description: The newly resurrected Bloodstrike team is sent against Cabbot's dad: the supervillian QUANTUM! Meanwhile, Cabbot is high in the mountains of Afghanistan fighting mummies?!

2012-05-21|2012-05-27.description:
AVX Tie-in!

Captain Marvel reborn to unite all Kree!

Captain Marvel, The Protector and Ms. Marvel vs the Secret Avengers!

Who is Minister Marvel and why has he drawn the Phoenix to the Kree homeworld?
2012-05-21|2012-05-27.name: Sacred Ground

2012-05-28|2012-06-03.description: "The Nocturnes" concludes here! Calvin Poole is a haunted man with a secret, but it's nothing compared to the secret he uncovers in a small Southern town. Plus, a major character steps back onto the stage!

2012-06-11|2012-06-17.description:
AVX TIE-IN! With the events of AVX raging around them, an Avenger betrays the team!

Editor's note: This story takes place before the events of AvX #4.
2012-06-11|2012-06-17.name: Kree Supremacy

2012-06-18|2012-06-24.description: AVX TIE-IN! Hope Summers journeys to the magical city of K'un L'un, home of the Iron Fist, to uncover her destiny! But will she conquer her future...or be consumed by it?
2012-06-18|2012-06-24.name: A Phoenix Rises In K'un Lun

2012-07-02|2012-07-08.description: Things are really rockin' in Seville, where the 99 Steps Foundation is throwing a party to get to know their new neighbors. The problem is, it isn't just the band that's doing the rockin' but Tremor, a villain with some earth shaking abilities. Oh, and there's an 800 pound gorilla in the room too.
2012-07-02|2012-07-08.name: Tremor Vs. The Singing Gorilla: A Prologue

2012-07-02|2012-07-08.description: Ever since they first met, Amon has been preparing Gwen for the coming of Xitalu, the Great Devourer from beyond space and time. But no one warned the rest of the people in town! And now that Xitalu is almost here, threatening to consume every living soul on Earth, will Gwen be able to do what’s necessary to save the world?
2012-07-02|2012-07-08.name: The End, Part 3

2012-07-09|2012-07-15.description:
X-Force land themselves somewhere you’ve never seen them.

A new member joins the team!

Rising star Julian Totino Tedesco (VENOM: CIRCLE OF FOUR, JOHN CARTER GODS OF MARS covers) joins the best creative team in comics for two issues!
2012-07-09|2012-07-15.name: The World Won't Stop Without You

2012-08-27|2012-09-02.description: The Outcast arc reaches its thunderous conclusion! Green Hornet has been set up for murder. He's seen his entire city turned against him. He's seen the foundations of everything he and his father have built in Century City damaged. Now, it's time to strike back. With the aid of a new hero, Green Hornet and Kato fight back to save their city, and their own legacies. Will Britt Reid reclaim his role as Century City's mysterious avenger, or will he be permanently labeled an outcast?

Venom, Scarlet Spider and the Micronauts fight to save a universe – but in the process, have doomed our own!

Cullen Bunn and Declan Shalvey bring you the pentultimate chapter of the mega-levolent masterpiece!

2012-12-03|2012-12-09.description: "Off the Menu" part 1 of 3. When Batman is called to investigate a disturbance in a defunct restaurant, he discovers that someone's recreating the chef's masterpieces. But the ingredient list is somewhat different this time.
2012-12-03|2012-12-09.name: Off the Menu, Part 1 of 3

2012-12-17|2012-12-23.description: Gord Cantrell, Kirby Hale, and Asher Cobb make for odd traveling companions. Each of them wants to find the guns for different reasons, but they are united against common enemies. Meanwhile, it's all-out war in the heart of a supernatural blizzard! Drake and Becky have been terrorized by the Wendigo spirit, but now they are taking the fight to the creature itself.
